notesStmt.note: Two additional documents (3 leaves) related to the case laid inside back cover.

msContents.summary: Interrogation in the trial of Oratio Molinari, accused of having rendered pregnant Johanna Lombardina, daughter of Antonio Lombardini. The trial was held in the Brosinopiano district of Arcisate, in the Lombardy region of Italy.

msItem.title: Vicecomitium in causa detentionis Oratii Molinarii nuncpatus il Suizzeretto
msItem.author: Lombardina, Johanna
Lombardini, Antonio
Molinari, Oratio

supportDesc.extent: 96 leaves, plus 3 leaves laid in : 293 x 202 (263 x 145) mm. bound to 293 x 205 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 96; [i], 1-95; contemporary foliation in ink, beginning on f. 2 (index on f. 1). Each folio stamped F1.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand, with signatures and affadavits in various other hands.

origin.p: Written in the district of Como, 1740-1741.
